Package: artma
Title: Automatic Replication Tools for Meta-Analysis
Version: 0.1.10
Authors@R: 
    person("Petr", "Čala", , "61505008@fsv.cuni.cz", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Author: Petr Čala [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Petr Čala <61505008@fsv.cuni.cz>
Description: This package provides a simple and unified interface for running a wide range of meta-analysis methods directly from your data. By inputting a data frame and specifying a few key options, users can effortlessly execute and compare multiple commonly used meta-analytic models. Designed to work out of the box, it enables researchers of all backgrounds to replicate and conduct their own meta-analyses without needing to manually implement each method. Ideal for transparency, reproducibility, and ease of use, the package streamlines the analytical workflow from data to results. For further methodological details see: Funnel plot method <https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1111/j.1467-6419.2009.00593.x>, Ioannidis et al. (2017) <http://pinguet.free.fr/ioannidis17.pdf>, Stanley et al. (2010) <doi:10.1198/tast.2009.08205>, Furukawa (2019) <https://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=3362053>, Allenby & Rossi (2006) <https://books.google.com/books?hl=en&lr=&id=RymGgxN3zD4C&oi=fnd&pg=PA418&dq=hierarchical+bayes&ots=a4t-KvUdua&sig=K7V5JgPF4_gJll2d7reATSQ8I-I>, Andrews & Kasy (2019) <https://www.aeaweb.org/doi/10.1257/aer.20180310>, Bom & Rachinger (2020) <https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.1002/jrsm.1352>, van Aert & van Assen (2018) <https://cloud.r-project.org/web/packages/puniform/puniform.pdf>, Gerber & Malhotra (2008) <https://citeseerx.ist.psu.edu/document?repid=rep1&type=pdf&doi=43eb85dd4af8c64cf6bacba73c39b1027606bcdf>, Elliot et al. (2022) <https://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/abs/10.3982/ECTA18583>, Irsova et al. (2023) <https://www.econstor.eu/handle/10419/268683>, Frequentist Model Averaging <https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0304407615000342>, or Robust Bayesian Model Averaging <https://github.com/FBartos/RoBMA>.
